---

<section
  class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 py-10 border-t border-[var(--border)] max-md:grid-cols-1"
>
  <div class="p-4 bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg">
    <h3 class="text-[13px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-[var(--bright)]">
      Live state, not pixels
    </h3>
    <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[var(--dim)]">
      blit tracks the full parsed terminal grid and sends only what changed —
      LZ4-compressed binary diffs. The browser gets real structured data:
      select text, resize freely, type into it. Each client is paced by its
      own render metrics so a phone on 3G never stalls a workstation on localhost.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="p-4 bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg">
    <h3 class="text-[13px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-[var(--bright)]">
      Share with one command
    </h3>
    <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[var(--dim)]">
      <code class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]">blit share</code> prints a URL anyone can open.
      WebRTC punches through NATs — no SSH keys, no port forwarding.
      Connect to named remote SSH hosts with <code class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]">blit remote add</code>.
      Auto-installs on first connection.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="p-4 bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg">
    <h3 class="text-[13px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-[var(--bright)]">
      Terminals as an API
    </h3>
    <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[var(--dim)]">
      Non-interactive subcommands for scripts and LLMs.
      <code class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]">blit terminal start</code>,
      <code class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]">show</code>,
      <code class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]">send</code>,
      <code class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]">wait --pattern</code>.
      We publish a <a href="https://install.blit.sh/SKILL.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--accent)] no-underline hover:underline">computer agent skill</a> — drop it straight into any AI agent.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="p-4 bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-lg">
    <h3 class="text-[13px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-[var(--bright)]">
      Headless Wayland compositor <span class="text-[10px] font-normal uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--accent)] opacity-70">Experimental</span>
    </h3>
    <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[var(--dim)]">
      On Linux, every blit terminal includes an experimental headless
      Wayland compositor. Launch GUI apps —
      <code class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]">blit terminal start foot</code> —
      then screenshot, click, and type into them via
      <code class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]">blit surface capture</code> /
      <code class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]">blit surface click</code>.
      Streamed as H.264 / AV1 video. Audio forwarded via PipeWire and
      streamed as Opus. No display, no GPU required.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
